defaultPrevalencedefaultAnecdotal evidence from homelessness services has long maintained that there is a large LGBT youth homeless 
defaultpopulation; t
defaulthere 
defaultis 
defaultalso some
default 
defaultsocial research suggesting 
defaulta sizeable disproportion
default of LGBT people in the youth homelessness population
default, particularly in urban areas with LGBT cultural hubs. 
defaultDunne et al (2002) found an estimate of 26% LG
defaultBT people among the y
defaultouth 
defaulthomelessness population from homeless agencies in London
default (this compares to an estimated 9% prevalence of LGBT people among the general population).
default Browne and Davis (2008) found a 
default22% 
defaultprevalence of 
defaulthomelessness among a sizeable sample of LGBT people l
defaultiving and working in Brighton (this compares to around 8% prevalence of homelessness within the general population).
default By contrast, in the US, where state support for homeless people is far lower, the estimated prevalence of LGBT people in t
defaulthe young homeless population is between 25% and 
default40% (
defaultKruks, 1991; Noel and Ochs, 2001; Cochran et al, 2002).
